---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words Containing W — Top Scoring W Words"
  description="Discover the highest-scoring Scrabble words containing W. Free list of top W words with point values and strategy tips for maximizing your W tile plays."
  keywords="scrabble words containing w, w words scrabble, words with w, high scoring w words, scrabble w strategy, scrabble word list"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Scrabble Words Containing W — Top Highest-Scoring W Words",
    "description": "Discover the highest-scoring Scrabble words containing W. Complete list with point values and strategy tips.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-14",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-containing-w" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the highest-scoring Scrabble word containing W?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "BEESWAX scores 19 points without premium squares. Other high-scoring W words include JIGSAW (17 points), POWWOW (17 points), and WAYWARD (17 points). W is worth 4 points, making it a solid mid-value tile." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many W tiles are in a Scrabble bag?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "There are two W tiles in a standard Scrabble set, each worth 4 points. W is versatile and appears commonly at the start of words, in WH- combinations, and in the middle of words like ELBOW and SHADOW." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What strategy works best for W tiles in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Pair W with other high-value tiles like X (BEESWAX, WAX) or J (JIGSAW). Double-W words like POWWOW, WILLOW, and WALLOW use both W tiles efficiently. W on a premium square is worth 8 (DLS) or 12 (TLS) points from one tile." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">More Letter Guides</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words Containing W — Top Highest-Scoring W Words</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        W is worth 4 points and appears on two tiles in the bag. It's one of the most versatile mid-value consonants in Scrabble, appearing naturally at the beginning of hundreds of words and combining powerfully with high-value tiles like X and J. Double-W words like POWWOW, WILLOW, and WALLOW let you deploy both tiles efficiently for strong scores.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top 10 Highest-Scoring Words Containing W</h2>
      <p>These are the most valuable words containing W, ranked by base point value. W paired with premium tiles and double-W plays deliver the best scores.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">#</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Length</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">BEESWAX</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">19</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">JIGSAW</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">POWWOW</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">WAYWARD</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">SHADOW</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">SWALLOW</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">WILLOW</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">WIDOW</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">WALLOW</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">ELBOW</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why W-Containing Words Are Versatile Scoring Tools</h2>
      <p>W is one of the most flexible mid-value tiles in Scrabble. At 4 points, it adds meaningful value to any word while being common enough in English to fit into hundreds of plays. W appears most naturally at the start of words (WILLOW, WIDOW, WAYWARD, WALLOW) but also works beautifully in the middle (BEESWAX, JIGSAW, POWWOW, SHADOW, SWALLOW) and occasionally at the end (ELBOW).</p>
      <p>The real power of W comes from its partnerships. W plus X creates BEESWAX (19 pts) — one of the highest-scoring W words available. W plus J gives you JIGSAW (17 pts). Double-W words are another strong avenue: POWWOW (17 pts), WAYWARD (17 pts), WILLOW (12 pts), and WALLOW (12 pts) all use two W tiles for efficient rack management. The WH- prefix (WHERE, WHILE, WHEAT) and -OW ending (ELBOW, SHADOW, WILLOW) provide reliable patterns you can build around whenever you draw W.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Pair W with high-value tiles:</strong> BEESWAX (W+X = 19 pts), JIGSAW (W+J = 17 pts) — combining W with premium letters creates top-scoring plays.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Double-W words clear your rack:</strong> POWWOW, WAYWARD, WILLOW, WALLOW — if you hold both W tiles, these words deploy them efficiently in one play.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>W on premium squares:</strong> W on DLS = 8 points, W on TLS = 12 points from one tile. Position W on premium squares whenever possible for maximum value.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>The -OW pattern is reliable:</strong> ELBOW, SHADOW, WILLOW, SWALLOW — the -OW ending appears in dozens of common words and hooks easily with S.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>WAX is a premium short play:</strong> WAX scores 13 points in just 3 letters. It's ideal for tight board positions and reaching premium squares.</span></li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-z/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Containing Z — Top Scoring Z Words</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-v/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Containing V — Top Scoring V Words</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-k/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Containing K — Top Scoring K Words</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Try our free Scrabble Word Finder — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
